=> Reading your code line by line 
- Code tracing 
* If-Else statements: statements that decide the program flow to trun based on the condirtion we are checking against 

Syntax:

if( condition) {
// some code to execute when condition is true
}
 * condition => must be a statement that returns boolean datatype

* Q : Can " if " statement be used alone without "else" statments?
-yes

* else-if statement:  this statemnt is used when we have few conditions to check before we use " else statement"

syntax
if(condition) {
// code

}
else if
